---
/**
 * rest-api/0007 · Figure 1 — "caching is two mechanisms": freshness reuses a
 * stored response with no network call; validation cheaply confirms one with a
 * bodyless 304 round-trip.
 *
 * Copied VERBATIM from docs/rest-api/lessons/0007-caching-and-conditional-requests.html
 * (figure + svg + figcaption incl. the footnote <sup>). Lives as an .astro
 * component because raw inline SVG with kebab-case attributes is unreliable
 * inside MDX but is plain HTML inside .astro. No arrowhead markers here, so no
 * local <defs> is needed.
 */
---

<figure>
    <svg
        viewBox="0 0 640 170"
        role="img"
        aria-label="HTTP caching has two halves: freshness reuses a stored response with no network call; validation cheaply confirms a stored response with a bodyless round-trip"
    >
        <g font-family="ui-sans-serif,system-ui,sans-serif">
            <text
                x="320"
                y="18"
                text-anchor="middle"
                font-size="12"
                font-weight="700"
                fill="#111110">CACHING IS TWO MECHANISMS — DON'T CONFLATE THEM</text
            >
            <rect x="14" y="38" width="290" height="96" rx="9" fill="#eef5ee" stroke="#2f5d3a"
            ></rect>
            <text
                x="159"
                y="60"
                text-anchor="middle"
                font-size="13"
                font-weight="700"
                fill="#2f5d3a">FRESHNESS</text
            >
            <text x="159" y="80" text-anchor="middle" font-size="10" fill="#244a2e"
                >Cache-Control: max-age=N</text
            >
            <text x="159" y="98" text-anchor="middle" font-size="9.5" fill="#244a2e"
                >reuse stored copy · ZERO network</text
            >
            <text x="159" y="116" text-anchor="middle" font-size="9.5" fill="#244a2e"
                >the common-case win</text
            >
            <rect x="336" y="38" width="290" height="96" rx="9" fill="#eef2f5" stroke="#1f3a5a"
            ></rect>
            <text
                x="481"
                y="60"
                text-anchor="middle"
                font-size="13"
                font-weight="700"
                fill="#1f3a5a">VALIDATION</text
            >
            <text x="481" y="80" text-anchor="middle" font-size="10" fill="#1f3a5a"
                >ETag / If-None-Match</text
            >
            <text x="481" y="98" text-anchor="middle" font-size="9.5" fill="#1f3a5a"
                >round-trip · NO body → 304</text
            >
            <text x="481" y="116" text-anchor="middle" font-size="9.5" fill="#1f3a5a"
                >the cheap fallback</text
            >
            <text x="320" y="156" text-anchor="middle" font-size="10.5" fill="#7a1f12"
                >Design with both: aggressive freshness for the common case, validation as the cheap
                fallback when freshness lapses.</text
            >
        </g>
    </svg>
    <figcaption>
        <strong>Freshness</strong> reuses a stored response with no call at all; <strong
            >validation</strong
        > cheaply confirms one with a bodyless round-trip.<sup><a href="#s1" id="r1">1</a></sup>
    </figcaption>
</figure>
